description:
&lt;p&gt;The development of Early Intervention Services remains a priority for the Trust. This is an exciting opportunity for practitioners with experience and enthusiasm in delivering psychosocial interventions to contribute to the continuing development of services for people and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service provides a comprehensive range of interventions to individuals who experience a first episode psychosis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post involves the provision of Psychosocial Interventions, including support around housing, benefits and groups for people experiencing their first episode of psychosis. A significant part of the role will be supporting care coordinators to implement care plans which will include cognitive behavioural approaches and family interventions. &lt;strong&gt;There is also an expectation that this post develops a comprehensive programme of group activities&lt;/strong&gt;. The following skills will be required for this post&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of working within a mental health setting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Committed to a recovery based approach promoting social inclusion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Development of a group programme around activity, sport and wellbeing interventions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enthusiastic about making links with colleagues as well as other agencies and have an interest in running groups for service users and there families.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working closely with the other Early Intervention Workers and members of the local Recovery and Intensive Support Team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will be based at the Coast Resource Centre in Weston-super-Mare. This is very Close to the M5 and is easily accessible from Bristol and surrounding areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a great opportunity to work in an exciting and developing area of mental health practice and is a good opportunity for career development and CPD requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Service Manager Susan Ham, 01934 523700.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email susanham@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
